						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Hamtaro126 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />IF Carry Set = BCS<br />IF Equal = BEQ<br />IF Less = BMI(?)</div><br /><br />The macro would actually change carry set to BCC and equal to BNE since I want to enter the block of code if the flag is set.<br />In normal 6502 assembly Less is BCC, greater or equal is BCS (after a CMP instruction). That is how I implement it in the macro at least - NESHLA used the N flag &gt;:(</div>

