						<div class="postbody">.error outputs a line number with the string.<br />.fatal stops the assembly, but doesn't give a line number. <br /><br />There are some minor issues with this too, but the worst error is if the branch is too far, ca65 won't tell you were the problem is in the main code, just in the macro. The branch generation could be changed to always use a jmp with a branch over and I've added an option to do that which isn't too complicated if anyone wants. It's too bad there is no way to decide if the branch is long or not in the macro code.<br /><br />I don't see a way to use cheap local labels due to the generation of normal labels from the if macro(s)</div>

